This paper deals with the accuracy of influence functions, which are commonly used in machine learning and data analysis. The paper discusses the effect of removing large groups of training points and how influence functions can still accurately predict the effect. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, but the most likely ones are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.ST (Statistics).
